Get Started

Frequently Asked Questions

Learn more from our frequently asked questions.

See more FAQs
Will I be eligible for treatment?

Patients are potentially eligible for endocannabinoid support treatment if they have a chronic condition and all other treatment modalities have failed to treat/improve their health concerns. Learn more.

How much do consultations cost?

Initial consultations cost $120, follow up consultations cost $60 and script rewrites where no appointment is required cost $20. Nurse consultations are complimentary. The cost of your medications is not included in these fees.

How do I become a patient?

Simply fill in our patient intake and screening forms and book your appointment. If you are not suitable for treatment, you will be given a full refund.

Why choose MiDispensary?

Our qualified healthcare practitioners are endocannabinoid support experts who can help you find the right treatment for your individual needs. Prioritising patient outcomes, compassionate care and alternative options, our Doctors are brand agnostic and prescribe to best suit your specific health requirements.

What pharmacies does MiDispensary work with?

We work with a number of pharmacies around the country as well as having a MiPharmacy onsite at our MiDispensary clinics. We can post medication anywhere in Australia or you can take your prescription to a pharmacy of your choice.

Doctors consultations are available Australia wide either in person or via telehealth Zoom consultation.

Book your appointment today to talk to one of our doctors!
